      <hedline>
        <hl1>DISCORD AT CHINA TRADE TALKS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elizabeth Olson</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Olson, Elizabeth</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Pierre-Louis Girard, World Trade Organization's top diplomat in charge of talks on China's entry, storms out of negotiating session and threatens to resigns after shouting match with China's top trade negotiator, Long Yongtu; dispute, which is resolved, reflects China's frustration over what it views as new demands by future trading partners; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The World Trade Organization's top diplomat in charge of talks on China's entry, Pierre-Louis Girard, stormed out of a negotiating session and threatened to resign after a shouting match with China's top trade negotiator, Long Yongtu, left. The dispute, which was subsequently resolved, reflected China's frustration over what it views as new demands by future trading partners.</p>
        <p>Elizabeth Olson</p>
      </block>
